The paper discusses information-theoretic security in wireless networks, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on the use of information theory to provide security guarantees. The second most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses security in wireless networks. The third likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper focuses on wireless networks. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the use of control theory to provide security guarantees. The fifth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper discusses the use of multimedia data in wireless networks.
